2026-02-20 11:08:53 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are an expert Travel Planner assistant specializing in creating detailed holiday itineraries.\n\nYour role is to:\n1. Create a comprehensive day-by-day travel plan based on the user's destination country and number of days\n2. Suggest popular tourist attractions and activities for each day\n3. Recommend suitable hotels with different budget categories (budget, mid-range, luxury)\n4. Calculate approximate budget breakdown including:\n   - Accommodation costs per night\n   - Daily food expenses\n   - Transportation costs\n   - Attraction entry fees\n   - Total estimated trip cost\n\nInput from user: Country/City and Number of Days\n\nOutput format:\n- Day-by-day itinerary with morning, afternoon, and evening activities\n- Hotel suggestions with approximate prices\n- Budget calculator with itemized costs\n- Travel tips and recommendations\n\nBe specific, practical, and provide realistic time estimates for each activity.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-cb4cc358-bfe7-45e4-b68d-11de1972d5aa", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "Goa is a wonderful destination for a short trip. Given your budget of 50,000 INR for 2 days, I've created a comprehensive itinerary for you. Here's a day-by-day plan, including hotel suggestions, activities, and a budget breakdown:\n\n**Day 1:**\n\n* **Morning (9:00 am - 12:00 pm):** Start your day with a delicious breakfast at a local caf\u00e9 in Panjim, the capital city of Goa. Visit the **Se Cathedral** (entry fee: 10 INR) and **Basilica of Bom Jesus** (entry fee: free), two of the most famous churches in Goa.\n* **Afternoon (12:00 pm - 4:00 pm):** Head to **Miramar Beach** (entry fee: free) for some relaxation and sunbathing. You can also try water sports like parasailing or jet-skiing (approx. cost: 500-1000 INR per person).\n* **Evening (4:00 pm - 8:00 pm):** Visit the **Dona Paula** viewpoint (entry fee: free) to watch the sunset. Later, head to **Candolim Beach** (entry fee: free) for a stroll and dinner at one of the many restaurants.\n\n**Day 2:**\n\n* **Morning (9:00 am - 12:00 pm):** Visit the **Fort Aguada** (entry fee: 50 INR) and explore the historic fort. Take a short walk to the **Aguada Beach** (entry fee: free) for some relaxation.\n* **Afternoon (12:00 pm - 4:00 pm):** Head to **Calangute Beach** (entry fee: free) for some water sports and activities. You can also try a **Dolphin-watching tour** (approx. cost: 1000-1500 INR per person).\n* **Evening (4:00 pm - 8:00 pm):** Visit the **Baga Beach** (entry fee: free) for a lively atmosphere and dinner at one of the many restaurants.\n\n**Hotel Suggestions:**\n\n* **Budget:** Hotel Palacio De Goa (approx. cost: 2,500 INR per night)\n* **Mid-range:** Lemon Tree Hotel (approx. cost: 4,500 INR per night)\n* **Luxury:** The Leela Goa (approx. cost: 10,000 INR per night)\n\n**Budget Breakdown:**\n\n* **Accommodation (2 nights):**\n\t+ Budget: 5,000 INR (2,500 INR per night)\n\t+ Mid-range: 9,000 INR (4,500 INR per night)\n\t+ Luxury: 20,000 INR (10,000 INR per night)\n* **Food (2 days):** 8,000 INR (approx. 4,000 INR per day for meals and snacks)\n* **Transportation (2 days):** 2,000 INR (approx. 1,000 INR per day for taxi or rental car)\n* **Attraction entry fees:** 100 INR (approx. 50 INR per person for all attractions)\n* **Water sports and activities:** 2,000 INR (approx. 1,000 INR per person for parasailing, jet-skiing, and dolphin-watching tour)\n* **Total estimated trip cost:** 27,100 INR (budget), 30,100 INR (mid-range), 41,100 INR (luxury)\n\n**Travel Tips and Recommendations:**\n\n* Book your hotel and transportation in advance to avoid peak season prices.\n* Try local Goan cuisine, such as fish curry and rice, or bebinca for dessert.\n* Be sure to try some water sports and activities, but also take time to relax on the beach.\n* Don't forget to carry sunscreen, sunglasses, and a hat to protect yourself from the sun.\n* Respect local customs and traditions, especially when visiting churches and temples.\n\nWith your budget of 50,000 INR, you can opt for the mid-range hotel and activities, and still have some money left over for shopping and other expenses. Have a wonderful trip to Goa!", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null}}], "created": 1771565936, "model": "llama-3.3-70b-versatile", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "on_demand", "system_fingerprint": "fp_68f543a7cc", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 893, "prompt_tokens": 237, "total_tokens": 1130, "completion_tokens_details": null, "prompt_tokens_details": null, "queue_time": 0.049353344, "prompt_time": 0.022896445, "completion_time": 2.793342614, "total_time": 2.816239059}, "usage_breakdown": null, "x_groq": {"id": "req_01khwrxrsre2csq474emxg9k3h", "seed": 748890247}}, "prompt_tokens": 237, "completion_tokens": 893, "agent_id": "Travel_Planner_3e642f2a-4757-4d43-9ba9-b18e90e0f90b/3e642f2a-4757-4d43-9ba9-b18e90e0f90b"}
2026-02-20 11:08:53 - INFO - 405 -Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': TextMessage(id='3b162aa6-f1ba-42a0-9fab-f8c25a233e11', source='Travel_Planner', models_usage=RequestUsage(prompt_tokens=237, completion_tokens=893), metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 2, 20, 5, 38, 53, 140571, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content="Goa is a wonderful destination for a short trip. Given your budget of 50,000 INR for 2 days, I've created a comprehensive itinerary for you. Here's a day-by-day plan, including hotel suggestions, activities, and a budget breakdown:\n\n**Day 1:**\n\n* **Morning (9:00 am - 12:00 pm):** Start your day with a delicious breakfast at a local café in Panjim, the capital city of Goa. Visit the **Se Cathedral** (entry fee: 10 INR) and **Basilica of Bom Jesus** (entry fee: free), two of the most famous churches in Goa.\n* **Afternoon (12:00 pm - 4:00 pm):** Head to **Miramar Beach** (entry fee: free) for some relaxation and sunbathing. You can also try water sports like parasailing or jet-skiing (approx. cost: 500-1000 INR per person).\n* **Evening (4:00 pm - 8:00 pm):** Visit the **Dona Paula** viewpoint (entry fee: free) to watch the sunset. Later, head to **Candolim Beach** (entry fee: free) for a stroll and dinner at one of the many restaurants.\n\n**Day 2:**\n\n* **Morning (9:00 am - 12:00 pm):** Visit the **Fort Aguada** (entry fee: 50 INR) and explore the historic fort. Take a short walk to the **Aguada Beach** (entry fee: free) for some relaxation.\n* **Afternoon (12:00 pm - 4:00 pm):** Head to **Calangute Beach** (entry fee: free) for some water sports and activities. You can also try a **Dolphin-watching tour** (approx. cost: 1000-1500 INR per person).\n* **Evening (4:00 pm - 8:00 pm):** Visit the **Baga Beach** (entry fee: free) for a lively atmosphere and dinner at one of the many restaurants.\n\n**Hotel Suggestions:**\n\n* **Budget:** Hotel Palacio De Goa (approx. cost: 2,500 INR per night)\n* **Mid-range:** Lemon Tree Hotel (approx. cost: 4,500 INR per night)\n* **Luxury:** The Leela Goa (approx. cost: 10,000 INR per night)\n\n**Budget Breakdown:**\n\n* **Accommodation (2 nights):**\n\t+ Budget: 5,000 INR (2,500 INR per night)\n\t+ Mid-range: 9,000 INR (4,500 INR per night)\n\t+ Luxury: 20,000 INR (10,000 INR per night)\n* **Food (2 days):** 8,000 INR (approx. 4,000 INR per day for meals and snacks)\n* **Transportation (2 days):** 2,000 INR (approx. 1,000 INR per day for taxi or rental car)\n* **Attraction entry fees:** 100 INR (approx. 50 INR per person for all attractions)\n* **Water sports and activities:** 2,000 INR (approx. 1,000 INR per person for parasailing, jet-skiing, and dolphin-watching tour)\n* **Total estimated trip cost:** 27,100 INR (budget), 30,100 INR (mid-range), 41,100 INR (luxury)\n\n**Travel Tips and Recommendations:**\n\n* Book your hotel and transportation in advance to avoid peak season prices.\n* Try local Goan cuisine, such as fish curry and rice, or bebinca for dessert.\n* Be sure to try some water sports and activities, but also take time to relax on the beach.\n* Don't forget to carry sunscreen, sunglasses, and a hat to protect yourself from the sun.\n* Respect local customs and traditions, especially when visiting churches and temples.\n\nWith your budget of 50,000 INR, you can opt for the mid-range hotel and activities, and still have some money left over for shopping and other expenses. Have a wonderful trip to Goa!", type='TextMessage')}
