2026-02-20 11:08:55 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [{"type": "function", "function": {"name": "tavily_tool", "description": " Tavily tool to search on web  related to the hotel, destination, activities, and other travel-related information.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"query": {"description": "query", "title": "Query", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["query"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "google_map_tool", "description": " Google Map tool to get distance and duration between source and destination.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"source": {"description": "source", "title": "Source", "type": "string"}, "destination": {"description": "destination", "title": "Destination", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["source", "destination"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "serper_tool", "description": " Serper tool to search on web  related to the hotel availability and other travel-related information.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"query": {"description": "query", "title": "Query", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["query"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are a meticulous Travel Research Validator who verifies and fact-checks travel itineraries.\n\nYour role is to validate the Travel Planner's itinerary using the following tools:\n\n1. Google Maps Tool (google_map_tool):\n   - Verify distances between locations (source to destination)\n   - Check realistic travel times between attractions\n   - Validate transportation feasibility\n   - Calculate driving/transit distances\n\n2. Tavily Tool (tavily_tool):\n   - Search for famous tourist spots and verify their existence\n   - Find current information about attractions\n   - Verify opening hours and seasonal availability\n   - Check for any travel advisories or updates\n\n3. Serper Tool (serper_tool):\n   - Verify real-time hotel availability\n   - Check current hotel prices and ratings\n   - Validate accommodation options suggested by planner\n   - Search for recent reviews and recommendations\n\nValidation checklist:\n- Are the attractions real and currently accessible?\n- Are travel times between locations realistic?\n- Are hotel suggestions available and prices accurate?\n- Is the daily schedule feasible (not too packed)?\n- Are cost estimates reasonable and up-to-date?\n- Are there any missing important details?\n\nFinal decision:\nIf the itinerary looks good and all validations pass, say \"APPROVE\".\nOtherwise, suggest specific corrections with evidence from your research.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Planner", "content": "Goa is a wonderful destination for a short trip. Given your budget of 50,000 INR for 2 days, I've created a comprehensive itinerary for you. Here's a day-by-day plan, including hotel suggestions, activities, and a budget breakdown:\n\n**Day 1:**\n\n* **Morning (9:00 am - 12:00 pm):** Start your day with a delicious breakfast at a local caf\u00e9 in Panjim, the capital city of Goa. Visit the **Se Cathedral** (entry fee: 10 INR) and **Basilica of Bom Jesus** (entry fee: free), two of the most famous churches in Goa.\n* **Afternoon (12:00 pm - 4:00 pm):** Head to **Miramar Beach** (entry fee: free) for some relaxation and sunbathing. You can also try water sports like parasailing or jet-skiing (approx. cost: 500-1000 INR per person).\n* **Evening (4:00 pm - 8:00 pm):** Visit the **Dona Paula** viewpoint (entry fee: free) to watch the sunset. Later, head to **Candolim Beach** (entry fee: free) for a stroll and dinner at one of the many restaurants.\n\n**Day 2:**\n\n* **Morning (9:00 am - 12:00 pm):** Visit the **Fort Aguada** (entry fee: 50 INR) and explore the historic fort. Take a short walk to the **Aguada Beach** (entry fee: free) for some relaxation.\n* **Afternoon (12:00 pm - 4:00 pm):** Head to **Calangute Beach** (entry fee: free) for some water sports and activities. You can also try a **Dolphin-watching tour** (approx. cost: 1000-1500 INR per person).\n* **Evening (4:00 pm - 8:00 pm):** Visit the **Baga Beach** (entry fee: free) for a lively atmosphere and dinner at one of the many restaurants.\n\n**Hotel Suggestions:**\n\n* **Budget:** Hotel Palacio De Goa (approx. cost: 2,500 INR per night)\n* **Mid-range:** Lemon Tree Hotel (approx. cost: 4,500 INR per night)\n* **Luxury:** The Leela Goa (approx. cost: 10,000 INR per night)\n\n**Budget Breakdown:**\n\n* **Accommodation (2 nights):**\n\t+ Budget: 5,000 INR (2,500 INR per night)\n\t+ Mid-range: 9,000 INR (4,500 INR per night)\n\t+ Luxury: 20,000 INR (10,000 INR per night)\n* **Food (2 days):** 8,000 INR (approx. 4,000 INR per day for meals and snacks)\n* **Transportation (2 days):** 2,000 INR (approx. 1,000 INR per day for taxi or rental car)\n* **Attraction entry fees:** 100 INR (approx. 50 INR per person for all attractions)\n* **Water sports and activities:** 2,000 INR (approx. 1,000 INR per person for parasailing, jet-skiing, and dolphin-watching tour)\n* **Total estimated trip cost:** 27,100 INR (budget), 30,100 INR (mid-range), 41,100 INR (luxury)\n\n**Travel Tips and Recommendations:**\n\n* Book your hotel and transportation in advance to avoid peak season prices.\n* Try local Goan cuisine, such as fish curry and rice, or bebinca for dessert.\n* Be sure to try some water sports and activities, but also take time to relax on the beach.\n* Don't forget to carry sunscreen, sunglasses, and a hat to protect yourself from the sun.\n* Respect local customs and traditions, especially when visiting churches and temples.\n\nWith your budget of 50,000 INR, you can opt for the mid-range hotel and activities, and still have some money left over for shopping and other expenses. Have a wonderful trip to Goa!"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-9ed73d65-1f06-4c60-ae14-01a8743954e0", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "yh570122g", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Goa tourist spots\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "e9j0rx5fk", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Se Cathedral entry fee\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "f1ma4ec41", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Basilica of Bom Jesus entry fee\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "h2jwnxkv5", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Miramar Beach activities\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "2aqpfn8wy", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Dona Paula viewpoint sunset time\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "sh8snm0kq", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Candolim Beach restaurants\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "b6b1hcmx3", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Fort Aguada entry fee\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "y5ts7ebws", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Aguada Beach activities\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "ffjgb726j", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Calangute Beach water sports\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "5bz2g5hxm", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Baga Beach restaurants\"}", "name": "tavily_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "fd9s85gbt", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Hotel Palacio De Goa availability\"}", "name": "serper_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "yrsepf8dh", "function": {"arguments": "{\"query\":\"Lemon Tree Hotel Goa availability\"}", "name": "serper_tool"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "5sfp7hvsx", "function": {"argumen